bin/
================

Binary blobs only. No buildable source lives here (that's src/, see
../src/) -- everything under this directory is either a pristine
upstream artifact or `make` output, never hand-edited.

Only three configs are considered finished/canonical and live directly
here: OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild/, t1_boot_fix/, tlb_fix/. Experimental/
in-progress variants live under _test/ (see _test/README if present, or
../src/_test/ for the corresponding sources); external reference-only
blobs with no corresponding src/ live under _reference/.

_reference/OpenSPARC_T1_original/
    Sun's original, unmodified 2006 OpenSPARC T1 "niagara" Legion release
    (GPLv2 -- see each file's own header). Kept exactly as shipped,
    including its own Makefile/Makefile.master and mixed source+blob
    layout (niagara/*.pdesc, *.hdesc, *.conf, *-md.bin, *-hv.bin) -- this
    is the one deliberate exception to the "blobs only" rule, since it's
    the ground-truth reference everything else is validated against.

OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild/
    Output of `make` in ../src/OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild/: the same original
    sources above, compiled with our own GNU-make-ported mdgen
    (github.com/unix0cc/mdbuild) instead of Sun's Solaris/Sun-Studio
    build. 1up-md.bin/1up-hv.bin here are verified byte-identical to
    _reference/OpenSPARC_T1_original/niagara/1up-{md,hv}.bin -- this is
    the toolchain fidelity proof. Flat layout (no "1up" subdirectory,
    2026-07-22 restructuring) since it's a single config.

t1_boot_fix/256/, t1_boot_fix/1024/
    Output of `make` in ../src/t1_boot_fix/256/ and ../src/t1_boot_fix/1024/:
    the boot-tested sun4v MD/hv-config for illumos/OpenSolaris snv_134,
    built by applying the fix patches in ../patches/t1_boot_fix/
    (memory/cpus/cache nodes + mmu-page-size-list/mmu-#va-bits platform
    props) on top of the original sources. 256/ and 1024/ differ only in
    mblock.size (MD) and GUEST() memsize (hv-config), matching the
    intended QEMU -m value.

_reference/1GiB-snv_77_1GiB-experimental/
    Externally-sourced, prebuilt 1GiB MD/hv-config for snv_77, pulled
    from github.com/artyom-tarasenko/qemu-sun4v-md, branch
    "1GiB-experimental", directory "1GiB-snv_77/". Not built by us --
    no corresponding src/ entry, since we don't have the .pdesc/.hdesc
    that produced it, only the compiled 1up-md.bin/1up-hv.bin. Kept
    as another deliberate exception to "blobs only via our own build",
    same rationale as _reference/OpenSPARC_T1_original/. Its
    nvram1/openboot.bin/q.bin/reset.bin are real files (that branch's
    own copies, not necessarily identical to fw_blobs/), and it has no
    netcons (the upstream directory didn't ship one).

Every other subdirectory also carries netcons, nvram1, openboot.bin,
q.bin, reset.bin -- symlinks to ../../fw_blobs/, the shared static
OBP/firmware blobs (not built by mdgen, just needed alongside the
MD/HV binaries for QEMU to boot).

Regenerating
------------
Never edit files under bin/ directly (other than _reference/, which is
frozen on purpose). To rebuild:

    cd ../src/<config>/
    make distclean   # wipes this directory's corresponding output
    make             # regenerates .bin/.txt + firmware symlinks here
